      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation software (Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2) must be validated under an FDA-recognized quality management system with documented V&V test suite results.",
      "rationale": "Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 is deployed under an ISO 13485-compliant QMS. Internal V&V test suite (2,400+ benchmark cases) is executed at each release; release notes and deviation reports are archived. Software change control procedures documented in SOP-SW-007. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2 for a Medium model risk."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Code verification benchmarks (patch test, beam bending, Hertzian contact) must be reproduced to within 1% of analytical solutions using the element formulations employed in the pedicle screw model.",
      "rationale": "Patch test, Timoshenko beam bending, and Hertzian contact benchmarks all reproduced to within 0.3% of analytical solutions using SOLID186 and CONTA174/TARGE170 element formulations. Benchmark reports archived in project document repository (DOC-CV-2023-041 through DOC-CV-2023-043)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study must demonstrate QoI change <2% between the production mesh and a refined mesh with at least 1.5× element density.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh convergence study performed: coarse (185k elements), medium/production (420k elements), fine (890k elements). Richardson extrapolation yields GCI < 0.8% for all three QoIs between medium and fine meshes. Production mesh selected as medium density; convergence criterion of <2% satisfied with margin. GCI report: DOC-MC-2023-017."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals must converge to force norm <1×10⁻⁴ and displacement norm <1×10⁻⁴ for all load steps; Newton-Raphson iteration counts must not exceed 25 per substep.",
      "rationale": "All 22 load steps across the compression-bending simulation converge with force norm <5×10⁻⁵ and displacement norm <3×10⁻⁵. Maximum Newton-Raphson iteration count is 14 per substep. Solver log files archived and reviewed; no unconverged substeps or bisection events recorded. Achieved level 2 exceeds required level 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup, boundary conditions, and load application by a second qualified analyst; documented checklist sign-off required.",
      "rationale": "Model setup independently reviewed by a second senior FEA analyst (not involved in original model construction) using a 47-item checklist covering geometry import, material assignment, contact definition, boundary conditions, and load application. All checklist items confirmed. Review report: DOC-UR-2023-009. One minor discrepancy (load application reference point offset by 0.05 mm) identified and corrected prior to final simulation runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model for Ti-6Al-4V must be justified against published material characterization data; contact formulation must be appropriate for the screw-rod interface.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening model for Ti-6Al-4V calibrated against uniaxial tensile data from ASTM E8 specimens machined from the same bar stock as the test implants (E=114 GPa, σ_y=880 MPa, E_t=1.2 GPa). Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient μ=0.25 used at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces, consistent with published tribological data for Ti alloy on Ti alloy under dry conditions. Model form selection documented in DOC-MF-2023-022."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material properties and geometric inputs must be traceable to measurements on the actual test specimens or to peer-reviewed published sources; traceability matrix required.",
      "rationale": "Geometry extracted from calibrated CMM measurements of three representative non-cannulated screws (mean dimensions used; dimensional variability ±0.02 mm). Ti-6Al-4V material properties from lot-specific tensile testing (n=5 specimens). Polyurethane foam block modulus from manufacturer datasheet confirmed by independent compression testing (n=3 blocks, CV=4.2%). Full traceability matrix in DOC-MI-2023-031 maps each model input to its measurement source and associated uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test specimens must be from the same design and manufacturing lot as the modeled device; dimensional inspection of a representative sample required.",
      "rationale": "All 11 test constructs assembled from non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screws from a single manufacturing lot (Lot 2023-NC-75-004). Dimensional inspection of 5 of 11 screws confirms critical dimensions (thread pitch, core diameter, head geometry) within ±0.03 mm of nominal CAD. UHMWPE rod from same extrusion lot. Construct assembly torque standardized at 8 N·m per protocol. Sample traceability documented in LAB-TR-2023-018."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions must span the clinically relevant range of loading rates and environmental conditions, or deviations must be justified.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single displacement rate (5 mm/min, ambient temperature, dry) per ASTM F1717. Clinically, loading is dynamic and the in vivo environment is saline at 37°C. Single test condition limits the achievable level to 2; the deviation is acknowledged and bounded by published literature showing <5% difference in Ti-6Al-4V yield properties between dry ambient and saline 37°C conditions. This factor is below the required level 3 and represents a documented limitation of the validation dataset."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs used in the validation simulation must match the measured experimental conditions; any deviations must be quantified and shown to have negligible effect on QoI.",
      "rationale": "Validation simulations use measured specimen dimensions, measured material properties, and measured assembly torque as inputs — not nominal design values. Foam block modulus for each test replicated using lot-specific measured value. Residual preload from assembly torque incorporated via a separate tightening simulation step. Equivalency confirmed for all 7 primary input parameters; maximum deviation between model input and measured value is 1.8% (foam modulus, one block). Equivalency report: DOC-EQ-2023-027."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) must be computed for each QoI; metric must be below 1.96 to satisfy the acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for all three QoIs: stiffness (E/uval=0.82), yield force (E/uval=1.14), force at 40 mm (E/uval=0.97). All values below 1.96. MAPE values: stiffness 3.1%, yield force 5.8%, force at 40 mm 4.3%. Comparison performed separately for each laboratory dataset; results consistent across labs (inter-lab variability in experimental data CV<6%). Output comparison report: DOC-OC-2023-035."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs selected for validation must be the same as or directly mechanistically linked to the QoIs used in the regulatory submission prediction.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the three QoIs specified in the ASTM F1717 standard and are the same quantities reported in the regulatory submission. No surrogate or proxy QoIs are used. Clinical relevance: construct stiffness relates to load sharing; yield force and force at 40 mm bound the structural safety margin against fatigue and catastrophic failure. QoI justification documented in DOC-QI-2023-011."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same device design, the same loading mode, and the same test standard as the COU; any differences must be justified.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities use the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw (identical to COU device), ASTM F1717 static compression-bending loading (identical to COU loading mode), and the same two-level construct configuration. The validation domain is therefore directly coincident with the COU. The only acknowledged gap is the single test condition (addressed under Test conditions factor). Relevance assessment: DOC-RA-2023-044."
    }
  ],
