    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves level 2 against a required level 3; this shortfall is accepted based on documented literature evidence bounding the environmental effect to <5% on yield properties, and on the conservative nature of the dry ambient test condition relative to in vivo loading. All three primary QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, MAPE < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is accepted as sufficiently credible for the stated COU.",
